body:
@rekhajoshm thanks for the patch, I found this issue is actually a bug in JDK7 with macOS:

http://crunchify.com/getting-java-net-unknownhostexception-nodename-nor-servname-provided-or-not-known-error-on-mac-os-x-update-your-privateetchosts-file/

so I feel this error does not necessarily require extra handling.

@auradkar Thanks for the review. Answering you questions:
2) Right, this should be the Phase 2 for KIP-4
1) The ultimate goal of KIP-4 is to have some unified CLI tool for all current .sh scripts. Thus TopicCommand will be transformed into this CLI at some point. This shouldn't be done now because, firstly, we don't have AdminClient, secondly, if something is wrong with this patch we will leave people no way to create/alter/delete topics - the old tool will be broken, the new one will not be ready.

@junrao I haven't added 2 things that you recommended yet.

1) I haven't add --addproducer --addconsumer options. I remember in review of KAFKA-2210 you recommended that we add these options so users don't have to call the CLI multiple times. This CLI is already looking very busy so I wanted to confirm that we still want to go ahead and add more options rathern than just adding the commands in help message.

2) I haven't created a map of what actions are meaningless (as of now) for a resource as you recommended in jira. I just noticed that when I went to the jira to mark it as in progress.
